Method Detail

onRequestPurchaseOk

void onRequestPurchaseOk(BillingManagerImpl.RequestPurchase request)
This is called when we receive a response code from the Google Play app for a RequestPurchase request that we made. This is NOT used for any purchase state changes. The order was sent successfully to the server.

Parameters:
request -

onRequestPurchaseCanceledByUser

void onRequestPurchaseCanceledByUser(BillingManagerImpl.RequestPurchase request)
This is called when we receive a response code from the Google Play app for a RequestPurchase request that we made. This is NOT used for any purchase state changes. The user didn't buy the item.

Parameters:
request -

onRequestPurchaseServiceUnavailable

void onRequestPurchaseServiceUnavailable(BillingManagerImpl.RequestPurchase request)
This is called when we receive a response code from the Google Play app for a RequestPurchase request that we made. This is NOT used for any purchase state changes. We couldn't connect to the the Google Play server (for example if the data connection is down).

Parameters:
request -

onRequestPurchaseBillingUnavailable

void onRequestPurchaseBillingUnavailable(BillingManagerImpl.RequestPurchase request)
This is called when we receive a response code from the Google Play app for a RequestPurchase request that we made. This is NOT used for any purchase state changes. In-app billing is not supported yet.

Parameters:
request -

onRequestPurchaseItemUnavailable

void onRequestPurchaseItemUnavailable(BillingManagerImpl.RequestPurchase request)
This is called when we receive a response code from the Google Play app for a RequestPurchase request that we made. This is NOT used for any purchase state changes. The item this app offered for sale does not exist (or is not published) in the server-side catalog.

Parameters:
request -

onRequestPurchaseError

void onRequestPurchaseError(BillingManagerImpl.RequestPurchase request)
This is called when we receive a response code from the Google Play app for a RequestPurchase request that we made. This is NOT used for any purchase state changes. Other errors (such as a server error).

Parameters:
request -

onRestoreTransactionsResponseOk

void onRestoreTransactionsResponseOk(BillingManagerImpl.RestoreTransactions request)
This is called when we receive a response code from the Google Play app for a RestoreTransactions request that we made. The request was successfully sent to the server.

request -

onRestoreTransactionsResponseError
